Might as well have been a slice of life newspaper comic (and that's basically how it was, 4 strips a month for 20+ years)

Computer nerd girl needs job, applies to vaguely computer related job, turns out it's a job at a porno studio. Includes a variety of early internet age jokes, from the freebie download speeds joke to ERPing in a chat room. Occasional dirty joke (One example is the implied scene where ZZ uses one of Sabrina's Transformers toys who turns into a train as a dildo) but it's kept pretty lighthearted. Schwartz was never really one for the dramatic, so there are no crazy out of left field plot twists that ruin the mood. It was like a news paper comic from the furry funnies; while it was running, you would binge up to the current date, and then check back at the first of the month for the next few 4 strips, then wait another month for the next four.

If you can stand his website design, I would recommend it, if only because it's pretty decent binge reading material. Twenty some years of 4 strips a month, and he maybe missed maybe four updates ever, and even then he made up for them by randomly uploading 6 at one time a few times over the years. Again, his work ethic is something to be admired.

I read up on his FurAffinity: It seems he plans on writing new self-contained substories and putting them on the comic website. So even if Sabrinas story has been told, he plans on expanding some side characters and such. Personally, I think the man is a work addict and couldn't NOT have the routine of a webcomic in his life.
